The paper proposes a novel domain adaptation method for image classification tasks, which involves leveraging labeled data in a related source domain to classify unlabeled data in a target domain. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves optimizing a unified model that incorporates data distribution constraints and constraints on hidden data geometric structure segmentation and alignment, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the experiments are carried out on standard DA benchmarks, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
